Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Stir in apples. Pour batter into well-greased and floured 13X9-inch baking pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick near center comes out clean. Combine sweetened condensed milk and sour cream in medium bowl; mix well. Stir in lemon juice. Remove cake from oven; spread sour cream mixture evenly over hot cake. Return to oven; bake 5 minutes or until set. Sprinkle with cinnamon (optional). Cool. Chill. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator.